            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", which put the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "public in general at risk",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/street-racing-honda-civic/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " of property damage, injury, and even a violent death.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/12/Motorious---2--1.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Twitter"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "During the weekend sweep, police impounded 5 vehicles allegedly involved in street races. One of the cars proudly displayed by authorities was a white ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "C5 Corvette",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/corvette-z06-driver-crashes/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". They also nabbed a BMW M3 and M4, plus a Nissan 350Z. A Chevy Camaro of unknown model year was also impounded.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/12/Motorious--1.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Twitter"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We’ve said it before and we’ll say it again: we don’t endorse street ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "racing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/ford-galaxie-pays-homage/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". If you’re going to send it on public roads, especially in a crowded city, be prepared to be ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "pulled over by the police",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/bumper-stickers/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". Not only will you be facing a hefty fine, you might also be doing some jail time, serving probation, and your car’s going to be impounded, which will mean some big fees for that service. Even worse, you could seriously injure or kill someone.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With COVID-19 shutdowns, some people have thought the relatively empty roads were perfect for racing. However, in many areas the streets aren’t so empty any more with kids, the elderly, and other innocents just trying to go wherever they need. If someone has to lose their car to learn the lesson that street racing is stupid, so be it.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/12/Motorious---1--1.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Twitter"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Over the weekend sweep, Metro Nashville PD said officers stopped 19 people for speeding, reckless driving, and other infractions. On Twitter some users were critical of the initiative, declaring “y’all got nerve” for supposedly just watching cars and wasting resources. Last time we checked, the police had the responsibility to make sure streets are safe, which includes busting street racers. Take it to the track or at least go somewhere so remote you won’t get busted or put anyone else in danger.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/MNPDNashville/status/1333100876324630529",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Our street racing initiative Sat night thru early today resulted in the impoundment of 5 cars for drag racing: a Chevy Camaro, a Chevy Corvette, a Nissan 350z, a BMW M3 &amp; a BMW M4. Officers made a total of 19 stops for speeding, reckless driving, etc. <a href=\"https://t.co/OwLfgL9fDs\">pic.twitter.com/OwLfgL9fDs</a></p>&mdash; Metro Nashville PD (@MNPDNashville) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MNPDNashville/status/1333100876324630529?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">November 29, 2020</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
